  "text": "Total cell proteins extracted from normal blood T cells [purified after CD2 magnetic beads selection and activated or not by CD3 (1µg/ml), CD28 (1µg/ml) and IL2 (100U/ml)], overnight serum deprivated DERL2 cells with or without CD3, CD28 and IL2 activation and overnight serum deprivated SUDHL4 cells with or without BCR stimulation (anti-Fab'2, 4µg/ml) were analyzed for the expression of Syk, phospho-Syk (Tyr525/526)(C87C1) (Cell Signaling technology) and β-actin (Sigma Aldrich). Immunoblotting was done as previously described [CITATION_1] .",
